{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Naom_Char_Incident",
  "title": "Massacre on Naom Char",
  "summary": "An Imperial recon expedition led by Commanders Danik Kreldin and Lanil Jast crash-lands their crippled Marauder-class cruiser in the jungles of Naom Char, with pilot Janos, private Sandor Woden, and soldier Lauranne among the dazed survivors. Unknown to them, the planet is home to a colony of escaped alien convicts ruled by the monstrous Brakath terrorist Verst Dejorn, who whips his horde -- including the brute Gorak, the Trandoshans Hora and Rika, and a murderous Rodian -- into a feeding frenzy against the stranded Imperials. As the planetary shield traps the Imperial relief ship Malignant in orbit, Danik leads the remnants of his force on a desperate three-kilometer push to destroy the shield generator hidden in an ancient temple. Sandor narrowly survives a prolonged duel with Gorak, killing the brute by sheer luck, while Danik personally battles Dejorn before detonating the temple and bringing the shield down. The Imperials are finally extracted and the planet bombarded, but Dejorn escapes by commandeering an Imperial dropship.",
